16. Auentinum montem: the Aventine, south-west of the Palatine and separated from it by the circus-valley, though included in the Servian wall, was outside the pomerium till the reign of Claudius (Tac. l.l.).

17. duabus causis : Gellius (l. l. ) reports that Messalla, a writer on augury, gave his authority to the second reason given here for exclusion.

19. non addixissent, ‘had not been favourable': a technical term of augury: cf. Livy xxvii 16, 15 Fabio auspicandi aues semel atque ilerum mm addixerunt. According to Livy's account, Remus first sighted six vultures from the Aventine, and then Romulus twelve from the Palatine; and number prevailed over priority (Livy i 6, 7).
